[1] The Netherlands
Date: Fri 20 Sep 2013
Source: NL Times [edited]
http://www.nltimes.nl/2013/09/20/twice-as-many-measles-cases/


At least 1458 people contracted the measles or still have it, reports the RIVM (Instituut voor Volksgezondheid en Milieu), the National Institute for Public Health and Environment, on Thu 19 Sep 2013.

Since last week, 110 new cases have been reported, more than twice as many as the week before, 9 of whom had to be admitted to the hospital. The real number of cases is probably higher, because most people who contract the measles don't go to their doctor. The measles epidemic has been going on since May this year [2013].

Although the RIVM finds it difficult to predict the course, the institute thinks the peak is yet to come, possibly in autumn [2013]. The majority of people who become infected live in the Bible Belt, the strip from Zeeland to West Overijssel, where many strict Calvinists live, who, for their faith, abandon vaccination.

A diagram of the measles epidemic, based on data from the RIVM, can be accessed at: http://www.nu.nl/files/datajournalistiek/graphics/highcharts/examples/mazelenhuidignieuw2012.htm.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
