[2] Russia (Astrakhan)
Date: Mon 16 Sep 2013 15
Source: RIA Novosti [in Russian, trans. abbrev. Mod.CP, edited]
http://ria.ru/society/20130916/963550587.html


On Mon 16 Sep 2013, medial staff of the Regional Infectious Diseases Hospital of the Astrachan State Medical Academy (ASMA) admitted another 3 students with suspected measles infection, bringing the total number of cases to 29. Previously, 26 students had been admitted with measles virus infection imported by foreign [i.e. non-resident] students from Dagestan.

The number of medical students who have become ill with measles in Astrakhan has grown to 26. According to an official, the academy decided to take immediate action to contain the outbreak and conducted mass vaccination of all students and staff. The necessity for vaccination was based on the presence of several students from Dagestan with suspected measles virus infection. The medical staff decided to extend vaccination to all patients and staff who did not have contraindications for vaccination.

Since many of the academy students had spent time in other health facilities as well as in the hospital, it was decided to extend vaccination to include all departments of the academy in addition to the hospital to avoid contact between patients and potentially infected students.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS <promed@promedmail.org>

[The Astrakhan Oblast is a federal subject of Russia. Its administrative center is the city of Astrakhan, population 1 010 073 (2010 census). Astrakhan is traversed by the northeasterly line of equal latitude and longitude. A map of Russia showing the location of Dagestan Oblast can be accessed at: http://www.luventicus.org/maps/russia/astrakhan.html. In general, the Russian Federation has a good record in the control of measles by vaccination. - Mod.CP

A ProMED-mail HealthMap can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1MnT.]

