[3] Russia (Tatarstan)
Date: Wed 18 Sep 2013
Source: Kazan News Agency [in Russian, machine trans. abbrv. & edited]
http://www.kzn.ru/news/40949-v-kazani-prinimayutsya-mery-protiv-obscherossijskoj-vspyshki-zabolevaemosti-koryu


Kazan, the capital of the Republic of Tatarstan, has been affected by the current outbreak of measles virus infection, which is affecting the whole of Russia.

Kazan municipal authorities have endorsed a plan to combat the spread of measles. According to figures cited by the city authorities, during the 1st 7 months of 2013, there were 720 cases of measles in 40 regions of the Republic. In Kazan, there have been 26 cases compared with 11 during the same period in 2012. This increase has been attributed to both the increasing incidence of measles in the countries of the European region and an increasing number of imported cases of the infection.

The spread of infection has occurred mainly in the unvaccinated sector of the population. In Tatarstan as a whole, 73.1 percent of people either have not been vaccinated against measles or have received only one vaccination.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS <promed@prommedmail.org>

[The Republic of Tatarstan is a federal subject of Russia located in the Volga Federal District. Its capital is the city of Kazan, which is one of Russia's larger and more prosperous cities. In the 2010 census, the population of Tatarstan was enumerated to be 3 786 488.

Maps showing the location of Tatarstan and Kazan can be accessed at: http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Atlas_of_Tatarstan. - Mod.CP

